all right?

129
00:08:10,941 --> 00:08:12,175
[Tomori] What kind?

130
00:08:12,242 --> 00:08:14,678
Sorry, I can't tell you that.

131
00:08:14,745 --> 00:08:18,481
Is it something you're willing
to lose your life to protect?

132
00:08:21,719 --> 00:08:24,121
[suspect] I'm looking
for Yusa Nishimori.

133
00:08:24,187 --> 00:08:26,557
[Tomori] And who asked you
to do that?

134
00:08:26,624 --> 00:08:27,825
[suspect] Taiyo TV.

135
00:08:27,891 --> 00:08:29,392
Right. What was their name?

136
00:08:29,459 --> 00:08:35,032
I don't know the person's name.
And that's the truth.

137
00:08:35,098 --> 00:08:39,570
Great, understood.
I'd already called for
an ambulance before you talked.

138
00:08:41,104 --> 00:08:43,073
[siren wails]

139
00:08:45,609 --> 00:08:49,246
[stranger] Hey.
What the hell are you guys?

140
00:08:50,848 --> 00:08:54,117
Just some people looking for
a woman named Yusa Nishimori.

141
00:08:54,184 --> 00:08:55,653
Her nickname is Yusarin!

142
00:08:55,719 --> 00:08:56,954
Why are you looking?

143
00:08:57,020 --> 00:08:58,956
I don't exactly know
the reason why,

144
00:08:59,022 --> 00:09:02,292
but it's a fact that
she's being chased, so we
thought we'd help her out.

145
00:09:02,359 --> 00:09:04,995
‐You guys know Yusa?
‐I'm a huge fan!

146
00:09:05,062 --> 00:09:06,864
‐[kick]
‐Would you stop interrupting?

147
00:09:06,930 --> 00:09:10,300
I was watching you.
How the hell did you
defeat that guy?

148
00:09:10,367 --> 00:09:12,736
[Tomori] We did it
using special abilities.

149
00:09:12,803 --> 00:09:15,839
Probably a lot like the ability
Nishimori has.

150
00:09:15,906 --> 00:09:18,542
[stranger] How do you know
about that?

151
00:09:18,609 --> 00:09:23,180
If you just trust us, I believe
we can help save her from harm.

152
00:09:23,246 --> 00:09:26,584
I see. I'm gonna need
to see some proof.

153
00:09:26,650 --> 00:09:29,587
Show me that you have
the same power that she does.

154
00:09:29,653 --> 00:09:32,556
It's not exactly
the same power, but...

155
00:09:32,623 --> 00:09:34,091
What the...?

156
00:09:34,157 --> 00:09:35,693
[Tomori] Here.

157
00:09:37,027 --> 00:09:39,129
Now do you believe
what I'm saying?

158
00:09:39,196 --> 00:09:42,833
Yeah. Come on,
I'll take you to her.

159
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:46,269
‐Though it's a bit confusing.
‐[Tomori] What do you mean
by that?

160
00:09:46,336 --> 00:09:47,705
Things got slightly complicated.

161
00:09:47,771 --> 00:09:51,341
I want you guys
to see for yourselves.

162
00:09:53,977 --> 00:09:56,814
[Tomori] So this
is a nightclub.

163
00:10:00,618 --> 00:10:04,154
