that wouldn't be good.

228
00:13:13,343 --> 00:13:15,746
[Tomori] I'm very surprised.

229
00:13:15,813 --> 00:13:18,949
It seems she can't call forth
the spirit on her own

230
00:13:19,016 --> 00:13:20,150
and that Misa is in control.

231
00:13:20,217 --> 00:13:21,885
So you got a problem with that?

232
00:13:21,952 --> 00:13:24,321
[Yu] <i>Another ability that's</i>
<i>somehow half‐assed.</i>

233
00:13:24,387 --> 00:13:27,725
That means she has
an unparalleled ability
to be possessed.

234
00:13:27,791 --> 00:13:32,262
And Misa, who possesses Yusa,
has pyrokinetic ability.

235
00:13:32,329 --> 00:13:33,631
Yeah.

236
00:13:33,697 --> 00:13:36,033
So, what is your relationship
with these two?

237
00:13:36,099 --> 00:13:40,037
They're my friends
from back when I was alive
and still causing trouble.

238
00:13:40,103 --> 00:13:44,341
[Tomori] Do you have any idea
why your little sister
is being chased?

239
00:13:44,407 --> 00:13:45,943
Yeah. 'Cause of this.

240
00:13:46,009 --> 00:13:49,212
Yusa accidentally brought this
home from some shoot.

241
00:13:49,279 --> 00:13:52,215
It belongs to one of
the bigger‐name producers
at the TV station.

242
00:13:52,282 --> 00:13:55,519
And she accidentally read
a text that was sent to it.

243
00:13:55,586 --> 00:13:58,722
Stealing company money,
organized crime connections.

244
00:13:58,789 --> 00:14:01,992
Stuff that would get the guy
arrested if it was taken
to the cops.

245
00:14:02,059 --> 00:14:04,361
[Tomori] Did you guys think
to turn the power off?

246
00:14:04,427 --> 00:14:06,930
Yeah. But it was on
until yesterday.

247
00:14:06,997 --> 00:14:08,766
[Tomori] Then they probably
already know

248
00:14:08,832 --> 00:14:12,035
that you're hiding somewhere
in this area from the GPS.

249
00:14:12,102 --> 00:14:15,338
Even if you gave
the phone back now,
you wouldn't be safe.

250
00:14:15,405 --> 00:14:17,575
And, if you gave it
to the police,

251
00:14:17,641 --> 00:14:19,943
it would look like Kurobane
sold out the producer

252
00:14:20,010 --> 00:14:22,479
and could keep her
from working in show biz.

253
00:14:22,546 --> 00:14:25,415
OK, I'll burn it down,
station and all.

254
00:14:25,482 --> 00:14:28,852
Are you stupid? You do that,
and your little sister
will end up in prison!

255
00:14:28,919 --> 00:14:31,088
Who the hell do you think
you are, huh?

256
00:14:31,154 --> 00:14:35,526
Do you really want to do
something that will land her
a stint in juvenile hall?

257
00:14:35,593 --> 00:14:38,228
That would make
absolutely no sense.

258
00:14:38,295 --> 00:14:41,632
[Tomori] Now please calm down.
You want to save your sister,
right?

259
00:14:41,699 --> 00:14:43,667
Huh? Yes, of course.

260
00:14:43,734 --> 00:14:45,235
Then we should help each other

261
00:14:45,302 --> 00:14:47,971
turn the tables on this guy
and threaten him instead.

262
00:14:48,038 --> 00:14:49,206
Huh?

263
00:14:49,272 --> 00:14:50,841
Can we win?

264
00:14:50,908 --> 00:14:53,644
I'm really good at creating
wonderfully devious plans

265
00:14:53,711 --> 00:14:56,346
for threatening others,
so you can trust me.

266
00:14:56,413 --> 00:14:58,315
You've got spunk.

267
00:14:58,381 --> 00:15:00,918
All right then,
I'll do whatever you say.

268
00:15:00,984 --> 00:15:03,386
I'd like the both of you
to help as well.

269
00:15:03,453 --> 00:15:06,724
[Sho] Of course we will,
if Misa says so.

270
00:15:06,790 --> 00:15:10,794
Oh my, I didn't fall asleep
again just now, did I?

271
00:15:10,861 --> 00:15:13,564
You must be really tired,
that's all, it's all right.

272
00:15:13,631 --> 00:15:16,199
Why don't you have some
roasted marshmallows and relax?

273
00:15:16,266 --> 00:15:20,003
[Yusa] Oh!
The marshmallows turned
into freshly roasted ones.

274
00:15:22,005 --> 00:15:23,907
[Takajo thinking]
<i>This is unbearable.</i>

275
00:15:23,974 --> 00:15:26,376
<i>I have no clue how I should</i>
<i>approach Yusarin from now on.</i>

276
00:15:26,443 --> 00:15:29,246
<i>Every picture I had in my head</i>
<i>about her has been blown.</i>

277
00:15:29,312 --> 00:15:30,748
[Yu]
<i>You're a scary guy.</i>

278
00:15:30,814 --> 00:15:33,551
First we should head to a shop
that sells work clothes.

279
00:15:33,617 --> 00:15:38,922
‐What for?
‐You two are going to need
a set of fireproof clothing.

280
00:15:41,959 --> 00:15:43,393
[vibrates]

281
00:15:43,460 --> 00:15:46,463
[line rings]

282
00:15:46,530 --> 00:15:48,766
‐[click]
‐[producer] <i>It's me.</i>

283
00:15:58,475 --> 00:15:59,677
Huh?

284
00:15:59,743 --> 00:16:02,613
So you finally showed up.

285
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:04,582
Realize that you couldn't
escape?

286
00:16:04,648 --> 00:16:08,686
[Yusa] Um, I really don't know
the reason why I'm being
chased so much.

287
00:16:08,752 --> 00:16:10,888
Did I do something wrong?

288
00:16:10,954 --> 00:16:12,723
[producer] Give me back
my phone!

289
00:16:12,790 --> 00:16:14,992
‐Is this the one?
‐[producer] Yeah.

290
00:16:15,058 --> 00:16:18,662
Even if I return it to you now,
am I, like, still in trouble?

291
00:16:18,729 --> 00:16:22,700
Whatever happens,
there's no future for you
in this industry anymore.

292
00:16:22,766 --> 00:16:25,636
There's no more future for me?

293
00:16:25,703 --> 00:16:29,507
Bastard! The one who has
no future is you!

294
00:16:29,573 --> 00:16:32,976
[groaning]

295
00:16:34,477 --> 00:16:37,114
I think I'll take out one more!

296
00:16:37,180 --> 00:16:39,617
[groaning]

297
00:16:39,683 --> 00:16:42,853
What the...
What the hell's going on?

298
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:45,723
You probably thought that
you had me cornered tonight,

299
00:16:45,789 --> 00:16:50,027
but you didn't realize that it
was me that had you cornered
all along.

300
00:16:50,093 --> 00:16:52,896
You really are senseless,
you know?

301
00:16:52,963 --> 00:16:54,865
[producer] What the hell
are you?

302
00:16:54,932 --> 00:16:57,868
I mean, are you really
Yusa Nishimori?

303
00:16:57,935 --> 00:17:01,672
Of course, I'm Yusa Nishimori,
the real Yusarin, who else?

304
00:17:01,739 --> 00:17:03,974
And in order to ensure
my success,

305
00:17:04,041 --> 00:17:08,178
I'm willing to kill anyone
who gets in my way, like them!

306
00:17:08,245 --> 00:17:10,013
[screams] That hurts!

307
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:14,151
This is getting boring.
I'll get rid of them
all at once.

308
00:17:16,987 --> 00:17:19,122
W‐Wait, wait, wait.
Just a minute. Hold on, please.

309
00:17:19,189 --> 00:17:23,126
‐Like I'm gonna wait!
‐[producer groans]

310
00:17:28,699 --> 00:17:30,601
What the hell is going on here?

311
00:17:30,668 --> 00:17:35,205
[Misa] I can bury you
in the shadows at any point
I want, understand?

312
00:17:35,272 --> 00:17:38,576
I get it, I give up.
Please, don't hurt me.

313
00:17:38,642 --> 00:17:40,678
[Misa] I'll give this
back to you.

314
00:17:40,744 --> 00:17:43,647
But there is no next time.

315
00:17:43,714 --> 00:17:46,449
I'll eradicate you
in a heartbeat.

316
00:17:46,517 --> 00:17:48,986
[producer whimpering]

317
00:17:50,688 --> 00:17:52,289
[both snicker]

318
00:17:56,093 --> 00:17:59,229
[Tomori] Thank you very much
for all your help.

319
00:17:59,296 --> 00:18:00,831
[Misa] No, you helped us.

320
00:18:00,898 --> 00:18:02,966
He believed that everything
that happened tonight

321
00:18:03,033 --> 00:18:04,835
was done by Yusa
all on her own.

322
00:18:04,902 --> 00:18:08,772
That producer will never dare
to go up against her again.

323
00:18:08,839 --> 00:18:13,043
No, I'm afraid everything is not
completely settled yet.

324
00:18:15,445 --> 00:18:18,816
And so I'd like you to transfer
into Hoshinoumi Academy

325
00:18:18,882 --> 00:18:21,519
and do everything you do
alongside us from now on.

326
00:18:21,585 --> 00:18:22,886
Why would she do that?

327
00:18:22,953 --> 00:18:25,088
Just like how
I explained earlier.

328
00:18:25,155 --> 00:18:28,458
If she gets caught
by the scientists, her days
as a guinea pig will begin

329
00:18:28,526 --> 00:18:32,095
and she will never be able
to return to a normal life,
understand?

330
00:18:32,162 --> 00:18:34,865
The condo next to our academy
will be the safest place

331
00:18:34,932 --> 00:18:39,069
for Kurobane to continue to grow
and live something
of a normal existence.

332
00:18:41,038 --> 00:18:43,440
[Misa] That's a life‐saving
story for Yusa.

333
00:18:43,507 --> 00:18:44,942
We'll do that.

334
00:18:45,008 --> 00:18:46,343
Hold on!

335
00:18:46,409 --> 00:18:47,678
Then, well...

336
00:18:47,745 --> 00:18:49,346
If Yusa's powers disappear,

337
00:18:49,412 --> 00:18:52,049
does that also mean
we'll never see Misa again?

338
00:18:52,115 --> 00:18:54,718
Yeah, that's exactly
what I wanted to ask.

339
00:18:54,785 --> 00:18:56,654
Well, I suppose
that will happen,

340
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:58,522
but she's already dead,
isn't she?

341
00:18:58,589 --> 00:19:01,659
Isn't it amazing that you were
able to see her at all?

342
00:19:01,725 --> 00:19:04,695
‐But‐‐
‐Sho, it's just like she says.

343
00:19:04,762 --> 00:19:06,129
In reality, she's not here.

344
00:19:06,196 --> 00:19:10,333
It's time to say goodbye
and let her go.

345
00:19:13,370 --> 00:19:17,240
Then at least let me tell her
how I truly feel about her.

346
00:19:17,307 --> 00:19:19,142
[Misa] Hmm?

347
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:27,417
Well, uh...
How do I put this?

348
00:19:27,484 --> 00:19:30,821
Now is when I can't
think of what I should say?

349
00:19:30,888 --> 00:19:34,792
Huh? Sho? Did you used to have
the hots for me?

350
00:19:36,126 --> 00:19:38,328
Uh...

351
00:19:38,395 --> 00:19:39,830
That's right.

352
00:19:39,897 --> 00:19:41,965
I really loved you, Misa.

353
00:19:42,032 --> 00:19:43,567
It's embarrassing to say...

354
00:19:43,634 --> 00:19:45,335
but I was in love

355
00:19:45,402 --> 00:19:49,039
and you passed away
before I could tell you.

356
00:19:49,106 --> 00:19:52,242
We had a motorcycle accident
while we were riding together.

357
00:19:52,309 --> 00:19:56,213
I was OK, but I was the one
that killed you.

358
00:19:56,279 --> 00:19:57,881
It's my fault.

359
00:19:57,948 --> 00:20:01,218
I see. It's all right.

360
00:20:01,284 --> 00:20:04,988
I made you harbor
such immense feelings inside,

361
00:20:05,055 --> 00:20:08,559
but I was the one that looked
for dangerous thrills.

362
00:20:08,626 --> 00:20:10,994
I reaped what I sowed.

363
00:20:13,797 --> 00:20:15,933
Don't cry,
that's not like you at all.

364
00:20:15,999 --> 00:20:18,802
Sho, forget about me.

365
00:20:18,869 --> 00:20:22,139
And starting tomorrow,
live your own life.

366
00:20:22,205 --> 00:20:25,342
And don't keep dragging
the dead into it.

367
00:20:25,408 --> 00:20:28,045
Otherwise, your life
will get screwed up

368
00:20:28,111 --> 00:20:31,682
and you won't be happy
in the future, OK?

369
00:20:31,749 --> 00:20:34,918
Jeez, you really are
a troublesome boy.

370
00:20:36,353 --> 00:20:37,588
Sho.

371
00:20:37,655 --> 00:20:39,489
[Sho] All right, Misa.

372
00:20:39,557 --> 00:20:43,561
I'll walk my own path
that you're not a part of.

373
00:20:43,627 --> 00:20:46,396
I'll sever my feelings
for you.

374
00:20:46,463 --> 00:20:48,165
And that's how I'll live on.

375
00:20:48,231 --> 00:20:50,834
Good. And I hope
that both of you

376
00:20:50,901 --> 00:20:52,670
live very long and happy lives.

377
00:20:52,736 --> 00:20:55,639
‐Yeah.
‐Sure.

378
00:20:55,706 --> 00:20:58,942
See ya!
And thanks for everything.

379
00:20:59,009 --> 00:21:02,412
'Cause it was
absolutely great!

380
00:21:05,148 --> 00:21:06,784
[Yu sighs]

381
00:21:06,850 --> 00:21:08,519
[Yu]
<i>It was a really long day.</i>

382
00:21:08,586 --> 00:21:10,453
<i>I'm exhausted.</i>

383
00:21:10,521 --> 00:21:12,022
You are so late!

384
00:21:12,089 --> 00:21:13,691
If you're going to be this late,

385
00:21:13,757 --> 00:21:15,593
I told you that I wanted you
to call!

386
00:21:15,659 --> 00:21:19,129
How about you?
What are you doing up
at this hour?

387
00:21:19,196 --> 00:21:21,599
Eating dinner together
as a family is a rule

388
00:21:21,665 --> 00:21:24,635
that's been passed down
the Otosaka house
for generations.

389
00:21:24,702 --> 00:21:28,338
Sorry, I was busy again today
doing work for
the student council.

390
00:21:28,405 --> 00:21:32,275
Aww. When you say that to me,
I can't say anything back.

391
00:21:32,342 --> 00:21:35,245
So tell me, what is it you made
for dinner tonight?

392
00:21:35,312 --> 00:21:38,816
I made a very satisfying
spaghetti with meat sauce.

393
00:21:40,818 --> 00:21:43,921
[soft music in background]

394
00:21:43,987 --> 00:21:47,858
Oh! It's How‐Low‐Hello again!
[giggles]

395
00:21:49,326 --> 00:21:52,162
‐[sighs]
‐[woman singing in Japanese]

396
00:21:55,032 --> 00:21:58,135
Wow, it really is the same
person that I met today.

397
00:21:58,201 --> 00:22:00,838
Huh? Who exactly
are you talking about?

398
00:22:00,904 --> 00:22:03,440
You know, Yusa Nishimori,
the actual person.

399
00:22:03,507 --> 00:22:06,844
You mean the real one?
So you've actually gotten
to meet Yusarin?

400
00:22:06,910 --> 00:22:10,781
[Yu] <i>Oh, crap!</i>
<i>But they didn't tell me</i>
<i>to stay quiet about this.</i>

401
00:22:10,848 --> 00:22:12,816
<i>So I guess I can tell her.</i>

402
00:22:12,883 --> 00:22:15,052
She's transferring
into my academy tomorrow.

403
00:22:15,118 --> 00:22:18,421
What? Oh, that makes me
so jealous!

404
00:22:18,488 --> 00:22:21,424
Do you think that maybe I'll be
able to meet her soon?

405
00:22:21,491 --> 00:22:24,194
Well, I guess that certainly is
a possibility.

406
00:22:24,261 --> 00:22:25,629
Wow!

407
00:22:25,696 --> 00:22:28,966
‐Oh, wow.
‐Let's start by cleaning up
your nosebleed.

408
00:22:29,032 --> 00:22:31,368
It's just something
that's so amazing!

409
00:22:31,434 --> 00:22:35,372
[Yu] <i>Come on,</i>
<i>you're getting way too excited</i>
<i>about this.</i>

410
00:22:36,439 --> 00:22:38,542
[theme song plays]

411
00:22:42,946 --> 00:22:45,015
[woman singing in Japanese]

